<br>
as for the conversion of the backslash to Åè and so forth, that's due to the layout of japanese keyboards (some of their keys are different than standard US keyboard).  It seems to be a carry over when you switch to japanese input, perhaps to keep things consistent. (For instance, in a japanese OS, instead of typing &quot;C: \ \windows\drivers\&quot; you would actually type &quot;CÅFÅèwindowsÅèdrivers&quot; and so forth).<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.sit.wisc.edu/~mamiller2/panda/panda3.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--> <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Mamonaku. 11ban sen ni  Panda densha ga mairimasu.  <!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Abunai desu kara, kiiro no sen no uchigawa made osagarikudasai.  </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> </strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
